=99s going to be able to learn. I thought the idea that you want your kids =
to be smarter and more successful than you was bullshit before I had one, b=
ut now I want that kid to blow me out of the water.=20
I=E2=80=99m like the Steve Buschemi, =E2=80=9Chow do you do, fellow kids?=
=E2=80=9D old guy of web3, this stuff will be native to him. Or maybe he=E2=
=80=99ll be onto web4 and roll his eyes when I talk about web3. I=E2=80=99l=
l ask him to do a TikTok dance, and he=E2=80=99ll roll his eyes and say, =
=E2=80=9CTikTok is for Zoomers.=E2=80=9D We=E2=80=99re going to inevitably =
hit a point when he=E2=80=99s explaining the latest trends to me; if Not Bo=
ring survives for another decade, it=E2=80=99ll likely be Dev behind the sc=
enes telling me what to write about, and correcting my embarrassing use of =
old terminology. Thanks in advance.=C2=A0
But I don=E2=80=99t want to wish away the present. Right now is pretty spec=
tacular. Even when I=E2=80=99m working every day, I get to wake up with Dev=
 in the morning, take him for a walk, pop downstairs and hang out between m=
eetings and calls. If he takes a step or says a word, I can drop what I=E2=
=80=99m doing and go see it for myself. We get to hang out as a family ever=
y day. I get to give him a bath and put him to bed every night. That wouldn=
=E2=80=99t have happened if we weren=E2=80=99t working from home, or if I w=
eren=E2=80=99t working for myself. None of this would be possible if Puja w=
eren=E2=80=99t holding it all down. Dev=E2=80=99s so lucky to have her as a=
 mom, and I=E2=80=99m so lucky to have her as a (much-better, more than equ=
al, far superior) partner.=C2=A0
The first year with Dev was the best, and the best is yet to come. Happy bi=
rthday little man.
